ntent': {'id': '7r3t8vk0', 'name': 'Ride FTP/kg', 'plots': [{'id': 3, 'agg': 'fill_in', 'fill': 'rgba(31,119,180, 0.3)', 'text': 'FTP/kg', 'type': 'line', 'field': 'ftp_kg', 'scale': 'watts_kg', 'stack': '', 'title': 'FTP/kg', 'filter': 'dec2_always', 'radius': 3, 'stroke': 'rgb(31,119,180)', 'filters': [{'id': 1, 'value': ['Ride', 'VirtualRide', 'MountainBikeRide', 'GravelRide'], 'field_id': 'type'}], 'markerValue': 'right-inline', 'strokeWidth': 1, 'showOnCalendar': False}, {'id': 4, 'agg': 'fill_in', 'fill': '#dd044780', 'text': 'eFTP/kg', 'type': 'line', 'field': 'eftp_kg', 'scale': 'watts_kg', 'stack': '', 'title': 'Estimated FTP/kg', 'filter': 'dec2_always', 'radius': 3, 'stroke': '#dd0447', 'filters': [{'id': 1, 'value': ['Ride', 'VirtualRide', 'MountainBikeRide', 'GravelRide'], 'field_id': 'type'}], 'markerValue': 'right-inline', 'strokeWidth': 1, 'showOnCalendar': False}], 'title': None, 'height': 55, 'yAxisMax': None, 'yAxisMin': None, 'y2AxisMax': None, 'y2AxisMin': None, 'y3AxisMax': None, 'y3AxisMin': None, 'yAxisLabel': 'Ride FTP/kg', 'y2AxisLabel': None, 'stackTo100Percent': None}, 'usage_count': 0, 'index': 12, 'hide_script': False, 'hidden_by_id': None, 'updated': '2025-02-06T08:42:04.543+00:00', 'from_athlete': {'id': None, 'name': None, 'profile_medium': '/no-profile-pic.png', 'city': None, 'state': None, 'country': None, 'timezone': None, 'sex': None, 'bio': None, 'website': None, 'email': None}, 'from_id': None}, {'id': 608293, 'athlete_id': '1914741', 'type': 'FITNESS_CHART', 'visibility': 'PRIVATE', 'name': 'Vo2max', 'description': None, 'image': None, 'content': {'id': '75omzlqo', 'name': 'Vo2max', 'plots': [{'id': 1, 'agg': 'none', 'min': None, 'band': 0, 'fill': 'rgba(23,190,207, 0.3)', 'text': 'VO2 Max', 'type': 'line', 'field': 'vo2max', 'gauge': True, 'scale': 'ml_kg_min', 'stack': '', 'title': 'Captured VO2 Max', 'extras': [], 'filter': 'dec1', 'radius': 3, 'stroke': 'rgb(23,190,207)', 'filters': [], 'i18nKey': 'VO2 Max', 'markerValue': 'top', 'strokeWidth': 1, 'i18nTitleKey': 'Captured VO2 Max', 'invertSubWellness': False}], 'title': None, 'height': 55, 'yAxisMax': None, 'yAxisMin': None, 'y2AxisMax': None, 'y2AxisMin': None, 'y3AxisMax': None, 'y3AxisMin': None, 'yAxisLabel': None, 'y2AxisLabel': None, 'stackTo100Percent': None}, 'usage_count': 0, 'index': 13, 'hide_script': False, 'hidden_by_id': None, 'updated': '2025-03-31T07:36:26.273+00:00', 'from_athlete': {'id': None, 'name': None, 'profile_medium': '/no-profile-pic.png', 'city': None, 'state': None, 'country': None, 'timezone': None, 'sex': None, 'bio': None, 'website': None, 'email': None}, 'from_id': None}, {'id': 835640, 'athlete_id': '1914741', 'type': 'FITNESS_CHART', 'visibility': 'PRIVATE', 'name': 'Acute:Chronic Workload Ratio', 'description': 'Acute:Chronic Workload Ratio is your fatigue divided by your fitness. It can be interpreted as follows: \n- 0;80- : Recovery or detraining\n- [0.80, 1.30]: Optimal workload and lowest relative injury risk; the safe zone\n- 1.50+ : Overloading and highest relative injury risk - \n\nMonitoring training and match loads is imperative to enhance performance and prevent injury. An effective monitoring protocol can provide important feedback to assist in training planning and periodization, optimize physical condition, and avoid injury.\n\nOne method that can provide this important ‘snapshot’ is the acute:chronic workload ratio (ACWR). This number is the ratio between how much workload has been done in the last 7 days (acute workload, fatigue) versus the average weekly workload that has been performed over the previous 28 days (chronic workload, fitness). In other words, it is how much workload has been performed in the last week compared to the previous month.\n\nThe ACWR ratio is calculated by dividing the acute workload (fatigue) by the chronic workload (fitness). For example, if an athlete ran 30km in the past 7 days (acute workload) and in the previous 4 weeks (28 days) they ran an average of 28.5km*, then you would simply divide the acute workload (30km) by the chronic workload (28.5km), resulting in an ACWR of 1.05. In other words, the athlete did 105% of the workload in the past week compared to what they did over the past 4 weeks – meaning they had a total workload increase of 5%.\n\n*Week 1 (25km) + Week 2 (30km) + Week 3 (32km) + Week 4 (27km)\n4-week average = 28.5km\n\nThe chronic workload values can change from 4 weeks, 6 weeks, or 8 weeks, etc., but it is important to understand that you can lose valuable insight if you choose a longer chronic workload value. With an 8-week average, for instance, it’s harder to see weekly changes compared to a 4-week average.\n\nHere the same parameters as intervals.icu have been chosen.', 'image': None, 'content': {'id': 'wn9cn0ra', 'name': 'Acute:Chronic Workload Ratio', 'plots': [{'id': 1, 'agg': 'moving_avg', 'min': None, 'band': 0, 'fill': '#50486180', 'text': 'ACWR', 'type': 'line', 'field': 'acwr', 'scale': 'acwr', 'stack': '', 'title': 'Acute:chronic workload ratio', 'extras': [{'id': 1, 'y1': 0, 'y2': 0.8, 'fill': '#1F77B44D', 'text': 'Recovery', 'type': 'bar', 'zone': 2, 'labelX': 'right', 'labelY': 'center', 'stroke': '#1F77B4FF', 'opacity': 0.3}, {'id': 2, 'y1': 0.8, 'y2': 1.3, 'fill': '#009E0066', 'text': 'Optimal', 'type': 'bar', 'zone': 2, 'labelX': 'right', 'labelY': 'center', 'stroke': '#009E00FF', 'opacity': 0.9}, {'id': 3, 'y1': 1.5, 'y2': 2.3, 'fill': '#D627284D', 'text': 'High risk', 'type': 'bar', 'zone': 2, 'labelX': 'right', 'labelY': 'center', 'stroke': '#DD292AFF', 'opacity': 0.3}, {'id': 4, 'y1': 1.3, 'y2': 1.5, 'fill': '#FF7F0E66', 'text': 'Careful', 'type': 'bar', 'zone': 2, 'labelX': 'right', 'labelY': 'center', 'stroke': '#FF7F0EFF', 'opacity': 0.3}], 'filter': 'dec2', 'future': True, 'radius': 3, 'stroke': '#504861FF', 'aggArgs': {'days': 1, 'factor': 1}, 'filters': [], 'i18nKey': 'ACWR', 'markerValue': 'right-inline', 'strokeWidth': 3, 'i18nTitleKey': 'Acute:chronic workload r